canonical:
  title: 泛舟遊晋州南江
  author: 崔咸一
  language: lzh
  text: 鷗鴨雙雙掠水飛映山紅倒碧琉璃畫工未意千般景盡入書生一首詩
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 泛舟遊晋州南江
  author: 崔咸一
  language: lzh
  text: 鷗鴨雙雙掠水飛。映山紅倒碧琉璃。畫工未意千般景。盡入書生一首詩。
korean:
  title: 범주유진주남강
  author: 최함일
  language: kor
  text: |-
    갈매기와 오리는 쌍쌍이 물을 나는데
    영산홍은 푸른 유리(강물)에 거꾸로 비추네
    화공은 모를 테지 이 온갖 경치가
    모두 서생의 한 수 시에 들어온 줄을
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0710&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Boating on the South River at Jinju
  author: Choe Ham-il
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Gulls and ducks skim the water in pairs,
    Azaleas mirrored upside-down in jade-green glass.
    No painter could dream of such thousand-fold beauty—
    All of it captured in one scholar's poem.
  footnotes:
    - Azaleas are traditional symbols of transient beauty in East Asian poetry. The 'jade-green glass' is the poet's vivid rendering of the water itself. 'One scholar's poem' refers to the poet-speaker, elevating verse above the visual arts as the supreme means of capturing nature's splendor.
